Begin with the lid and work your way down and around the teapot in a swirling, descending motion. Add a symbol or mark to denote a break in between quotes. A simple dot (. ), asterisk (*), tilde or hyphen (~ or -) in between the quotes will suffice. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/55/Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/55/Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Change pen colors in between quotes (if using different colors). For example, write one quote in blue and the next quote in black. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/57/Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/57/Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Take breaks in between quotes so your hand does not get tired––you risk leaning into the ink and smudging it. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/87/Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/87/Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Aim to maintain a consistent word shape and design. Write words close together in order to fit all your quotes on the teapot. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/75/Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/75/Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Create-a-Quote-Teapot-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
